name: Allsafe Timeline
htmlstr:
• Step 1

    Pre-test

    Take the 10-question pre-test to gauge your knowledge before you start. Do not worry about your score here! This is your starting point. Expected time: 10 minutes.

  • Step 2

    Interactive Case Scenario

    You will learn the concepts of the preoperative evaluation of appendicitis through an interactive case scenario. This is not meant to be a test but rather the vehicle for your learning. Take this as many times as you want! You will need a perfect score in order to move on to the next part of the module. Expected time: 1 hour.

  • Step 3

    Psychomotor Instruction and Training

    Watch the expert paradigm of one of our experts performing the simulation in the box trainer. Watch this as many times as you need to. Expected time: 10 minutes.

  • Step 4

    The Build

    Build the box trainer and simulation. Test the video connection. This box trainer can be used for multiple modules for different laparoscopic surgeries. Please save this box for future use so you do not need to build it again! Expected time: 1 hour

  • Step 5

    Self Review

    Rate your own video using our assessment tool for immediate feedback. Expected Review: 5 min.

  • Step 6

    Peer Review

    Review a video of peers performing this same simulation (You will receive an email when a video is ready for review). Use our proficiency checklist to guide your review. Reviewing and assessing the work of others is a great way to learn! Expected time: 30 minutes.

  • Step 7

    Post-test

    Take the 10-question post-test to gauge your knowledge after you've completed the module. Expected time: 10 minutes.

  • Step 8

    Survey

    Take our learning survey to help us understand your perceived confidence and competence after completing our module. Help us make this module even better. Expected time: 5 minutes.

  • Step 9

    Certification and Feedback

    You will receive your ALL-SAFE Certificate of Completion through the email you used to register for the site after your videos have been reviewed. You will also receive formative feedback from the individuals who have reviewed your video. Let the learning continue!
